#: .\modinfo.json
msgid "The Vermilion Mod"
msgstr "硃紅模組"

#. ~ Description for The Vermilion Mod
#: .\modinfo.json
msgid ""
"Adds a random assortment of over-the-top weapons, gear and risqué items for "
"the depraved."
msgstr "為墮落者添加一系列隨機的誇張武器、裝備和挑逗物品。"

#: .\ver_ammo.json .\ver_ammo_types.json
msgid "14.5x114mm"
msgid_plural "14.5x114mm"
msgstr[0] "14.5x114毫米"

#. ~ Description for {'str': '14.5x114mm', 'str_pl': '14.5x114mm'}
#: .\ver_ammo.json
msgid ""
"A large proprietary cartridge for the PTRS-41 anti-tank rifle. Packs a hell "
"of a punch, but it has limited use."
msgstr "PTRS-41反坦克步槍專用的大型彈藥。威力巨大，但用途有限。"

#: .\ver_ammo.json
msgid "reloaded 14.5x114mm"
msgid_plural "reloaded 14.5x114mms"
msgstr[0] "重裝填的14.5x114毫米"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'reloaded 14.5x114mm'}
#: .\ver_ammo.json
msgid ""
"A large proprietary cartridge for the PTRS-41 anti-tank rifle. Packs a hell "
"of a punch, but it has limited use. This one has been hand-reloaded."
msgstr "PTRS-41反坦克步槍專用的大型彈藥。威力巨大，但用途有限。此彈藥為手工重裝填。"

#: .\ver_ammo.json
msgid "14.5x114mm casing"
msgid_plural "14.5x114mm casings"
msgstr[0] "14.5x114毫米彈殼"

#. ~ Description for {'str': '14.5x114mm casing'}
#: .\ver_ammo.json
msgid "A large, empty casing from a 14.5x114mm round."
msgstr "14.5x114毫米子彈的大型空彈殼。"

#: .\ver_ammo.json
msgid "explosive rail"
msgid_plural "explosive rails"
msgstr[0] "爆炸性導軌"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'explosive rail'}
#: .\ver_ammo.json
msgid ""
"A short piece of ferromagnetic rebar which has been straightened. A small, "
"crude RDX-filled warhead has been installed on the tip, causing a small "
"explosion on impact. Could be used as a projectile by a sufficiently "
"powerful electromagnetic weapon."
msgstr "一段被拉直的鐵磁性鋼筋。尖端安裝了一個粗糙的RDX填充彈頭，撞擊時會引起小爆炸。可由足夠強大的電磁武器用作彈丸。"

#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid "bomb suit"
msgid_plural "bomb suits"
msgstr[0] "防爆服"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'bomb suit', 'str_pl': 'bomb suits'}
#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid ""
"A thick and bulky armored suit used by EOD operators during bomb disposals. "
"It offers excellent protection against evironmental dangers and ballistics, "
"but is very cumbersome and hot to wear. It also lacks any gloves, leaving "
"your hands exposed."
msgstr "EOD操作員在拆彈時使用的厚重裝甲服。提供出色的環境和彈道防護，但穿著非常笨重悶熱。且無手套，手部暴露在外。"

#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid "skimpy one-piece string swimsuit"
msgid_plural "skimpy one-piece string swimsuits"
msgstr[0] "暴露的連體細繩泳裝"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'skimpy one-piece string swimsuit', 'str_pl':
#. 'skimpy one-piece string swimsuits'}
#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid ""
"A women's one-piece 'swimsuit' that consists of skintight string and "
"miniscule patches of ruffled blue and white striped cloth, barely covering "
"anything private."
msgstr "女士連體“泳裝”，由緊身細繩和極小的藍白條紋褶皺布片組成，幾乎未遮蓋任何私密部位。"

#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid "ofuda pasties"
msgid_plural "ofuda pastiess"
msgstr[0] "御札乳貼"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'ofuda pasties'}
#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid ""
"A pair of paper talismans from a Shinto shrine meant to ward off evil, with "
"an adhesive backside to make them stick onto surfaces. As much as you'd want"
" to, these talismans won't help ward off the hordes of undead, so naturally "
"the next thing to do is to wear them. Maybe the old gods haven't left yet "
"and you'll receive protection?"
msgstr ""
"一對來自神道神社的紙質護符，用於驅邪，背面有粘性可粘貼於表面。儘管你希望如此，這些護符無法驅散成群的亡靈，因此自然的選擇是佩戴它們。或許古老的神明尚未離去，你會獲得庇護？"

#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid "ofuda maebari"
msgid_plural "ofuda maebaris"
msgstr[0] "御札前貼"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'ofuda maebari'}
#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid ""
"A paper talisman from a Shinto shrine meant to ward off evil, with an "
"adhesive backside to make it stick onto surfaces. As much as you'd want to, "
"this talisman won't help ward off the hordes of undead, so naturally the "
"next thing to do is to wear it. The last line in divine protection."
msgstr ""
"來自神道神社的紙質護符，用於驅邪，背面有粘性可粘貼於表面。儘管你希望如此，此護符無法驅散成群的亡靈，因此自然的選擇是佩戴它。這是神聖庇護的最後防線。"

#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid "tactical eyepatch"
msgid_plural "tactical eyepatches"
msgstr[0] "戰術眼罩"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'tactical eyepatch', 'str_pl': 'tactical
#. eyepatches'}
#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid ""
"A large black strip of neoprene stamped with Prism Block's logo on the front"
" meant to be wrapped around the head, covering one eye and then some. "
"Inserted on the inside is a small crystal screen, streaming real time "
"footage with sophisticated targeting adjusters from the ultra HD bite-sized "
"camera on the outer side of the eyepatch. Does not bring vision to a blind "
"eye."
msgstr ""
"一條印有Prism "
"Block標誌的大型黑色氯丁橡膠帶，可纏繞頭部，覆蓋一隻眼睛及周圍。內側嵌有小水晶屏，從眼罩外側的超高清微型攝像頭實時傳輸畫面，並配有精密瞄準調節器。無法為失明的眼睛恢復視力。"

#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid "PB staff armband"
msgid_plural "PB staff armbands"
msgstr[0] "PB員工臂章"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'PB staff armband', 'str_pl': 'PB staff
#. armbands'}
#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid ""
"A flexible piece of clear plastic that can be clipped around the arm. "
"Clipping it turns it on, lighting the plastic in green with the word 'STAFF'"
" and Prism Block's logo slowly rotating around the length of the armband."
msgstr "一塊可彎曲的透明塑料片，可夾在手臂上。夾上即啟動，塑料發出綠光，顯示“員工”字樣，Prism Block標誌沿臂章長度緩慢旋轉。"

#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid "PB medical armband"
msgid_plural "PB medical armbands"
msgstr[0] "PB醫療臂章"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'PB medical armband', 'str_pl': 'PB medical
#. armbands'}
#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid ""
"A flexible piece of clear plastic that can be clipped around the arm. "
"Clipping it turns it on, lighting the plastic in red with the word 'MEDIC' "
"and Prism Block's logo slowly rotating around the length of the armband."
msgstr "一塊可彎曲的透明塑料片，可夾在手臂上。夾上即啟動，塑料發出紅光，顯示“醫療”字樣，Prism Block標誌沿臂章長度緩慢旋轉。"

#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid "PB security armband"
msgid_plural "PB security armbands"
msgstr[0] "PB安保臂章"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'PB security armband', 'str_pl': 'PB security
#. armbands'}
#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid ""
"A flexible piece of clear plastic that can be clipped around the arm. "
"Clipping it turns it on, lighting the plastic in yellow with the word "
"'SECURITY' and Prism Block's logo slowly rotating around the length of the "
"armband."
msgstr "一塊可彎曲的透明塑料片，可夾在手臂上。夾上即啟動，塑料發出黃光，顯示“安保”字樣，Prism Block標誌沿臂章長度緩慢旋轉。"

#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid "PB science armband"
msgid_plural "PB science armbands"
msgstr[0] "PB科研臂章"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'PB science armband', 'str_pl': 'PB science
#. armbands'}
#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid ""
"A flexible piece of clear plastic that can be clipped around the arm. "
"Clipping it turns it on, lighting the plastic in blue with the word "
"'SCIENCE' and Prism Block's logo slowly rotating around the length of the "
"armband."
msgstr "一塊可彎曲的透明塑料片，可夾在手臂上。夾上即啟動，塑料發出藍光，顯示“科研”字樣，Prism Block標誌沿臂章長度緩慢旋轉。"

#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid "PB security armor"
msgid_plural "PB security armors"
msgstr[0] "PB安保裝甲"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'PB security armor', 'str_pl': 'PB security
#. armors'}
#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid ""
"Standard set of armor used by the Prism Block security staff. Consists of a "
"black curve-hugging skintight neoprene bodysuit with an outer layer of white"
" thick alloy armor covering the torso, arms and legs, with unarmored bits at"
" the joints. 'SECURITY' is written on the left side of the breastplate."
msgstr ""
"稜鏡區塊安保人員使用的標準裝甲套裝。由一件黑色緊身氯丁橡膠連體衣構成，外層覆蓋著白色厚合金裝甲，保護軀幹、手臂和腿部，關節處為無裝甲部分。胸甲左側印有“SECURITY”字樣。"

#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid "PB security helmet"
msgid_plural "PB security helmets"
msgstr[0] "PB安保頭盔"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'PB security helmet', 'str_pl': 'PB security
#. helmets'}
#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid ""
"Standard issue helmet used by the Prism Block security staff. Consists of a "
"sturdy, if somewhat bulky looking closed helmet that covers the entire head "
"with a round, mirrored visor that covers the face and curves upwards to the "
"top of the head."
msgstr "稜鏡區塊安保人員使用的標準制式頭盔。由一頂堅固但略顯笨重的封閉式頭盔構成，覆蓋整個頭部，配有一個圓形鏡面面罩，覆蓋面部並向上彎曲至頭頂。"

#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid "PB traitor's suit"
msgid_plural "PB traitor's suit"
msgstr[0] "PB叛徒套裝"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "PB traitor's suit", 'str_pl': "PB traitor's
#. suit"}
#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid ""
"A pair of elastic suspenders sewn together to form an X-shape over the "
"torso, with their ends then sewn onto the heavily tattered remains of a "
"Prism Block lab coat, its sleeves tied together around the waist and the "
"rest of the coat acting as a waist cape, as it is much too worn down to be "
"worn as a regular coat. On the sleeve-belt is a Prism Block ID tag belonging"
" to a 'Shion O.'"
msgstr ""
"兩條彈性揹帶縫在一起，在軀幹上形成X形，末端縫在一件嚴重破損的稜鏡區塊實驗袍殘骸上。袖子在腰間繫在一起，其餘部分充當腰披風，因為它磨損得太厲害，無法作為常規外套穿著。袖帶上掛著一個稜鏡區塊身份標籤，屬於“Shion"
" O.”。"

#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid "PB traitor's stompers"
msgid_plural "PB traitor's stomperss"
msgstr[0] "PB叛徒踐踏靴"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "PB traitor's stompers"}
#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid ""
"These might've once belonged to a soldier, but it's hard to say anymore. A "
"pair of patched up, but sturdy looking kevlar and leather boots with steel "
"reinforced heels for extra stomping strength."
msgstr "這雙靴子可能曾屬於一名士兵，但現在很難說清了。一雙修補過但看起來堅固的凱夫拉和皮革靴子，帶有鋼製加固鞋跟，以增強踐踏力量。"

#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid "PB traitor's pants"
msgid_plural "PB traitor's pantss"
msgstr[0] "PB叛徒長褲"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "PB traitor's pants"}
#: .\ver_armor.json
msgid ""
"A tough pair of baggy weathered pants in woodland camo with kevlar patches "
"on the knees."
msgstr "一條堅韌的寬鬆風化長褲，採用林地迷彩，膝蓋處有凱夫拉補丁。"

#: .\ver_books.json
msgid "binder-CLASSIFIED #1117 CQC prototype"
msgid_plural "binder-CLASSIFIED #1117 CQC prototypes"
msgstr[0] "活頁夾-機密 #1117 CQC原型"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'binder-CLASSIFIED #1117 CQC prototype',
#. 'str_pl': 'binder-CLASSIFIED #1117 CQC prototypes'}
#: .\ver_books.json
msgid ""
"A thick binder filled with technical documents with coffee stains seemingly "
"on every page. There's something about teaching bionic soldiers on how to "
"use a special blade written in here."
msgstr "一本厚厚的活頁夾，裝滿了技術文檔，似乎每一頁都有咖啡漬。裡面寫著一些關於教導仿生士兵如何使用特殊刀刃的內容。"

#: .\ver_books.json
msgid "Prism Block leaflet"
msgid_plural "Prism Block leaflets"
msgstr[0] "稜鏡區塊宣傳冊"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Prism Block leaflet', 'str_pl': 'Prism Block
#. leaflets'}
#: .\ver_books.json
msgid ""
"A double-sided leaflet that opens annoyingly wide, cataloging weird and "
"bizarre high-tech home appliances on one side and military and law "
"enforcement equipment on the other side."
msgstr "一份雙面宣傳冊，展開時寬得令人惱火，一面 cataloging 奇怪詭異的高科技家用電器，另一面 cataloging 軍事和執法裝備。"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Prism Block leaflet', 'str_pl': 'Prism Block
#. leaflets'}
#: .\ver_books.json
msgid ""
"A double-sided leaflet that opens annoyingly wide, cataloging weird and "
"bizarre high-tech home appliances on one side and military and law "
"enforcement equipment on the other side. Someone has attached post-it notes "
"and scribbled instructions on how to make homemade variants of some of the "
"equipment, and it should be pretty easy for someone smart enough to figure "
"out how to build them. There's a drawing of a canine-eared person's head "
"giving a smug grin while holding up a victory sign decorating the last page."
msgstr ""
"一份雙面宣傳冊，展開時寬得令人惱火，一面 cataloging 奇怪詭異的高科技家用電器，另一面 cataloging "
"軍事和執法裝備。有人貼了便利貼並潦草地寫下了如何自制其中一些裝備的說明，對於足夠聰明的人來說，應該很容易弄清楚如何製造它們。最後一頁裝飾著一幅畫，畫中是一個長著犬耳的人頭，帶著得意的笑容，比著勝利的手勢。"

#: .\ver_gunmods.json
msgid "ceramic blade"
msgid_plural "ceramic blades"
msgstr[0] "陶瓷刀刃"

#: .\ver_gunmods.json
msgid ""
"A welded meter-long reinforced ceramic blade for the S-01 Rail Accelerator "
"mk2, poking backwards like a reverse bayonet, where the stock should be. The"
" blade makes it impossible to rest the launcher against your shoulder. If "
"you somehow manage to swing the Rail Accelerator at an enemy, be sure to hit"
" them with this."
msgstr ""
"一根焊接的一米長強化陶瓷刀刃，用於S-01軌道加速器mk2，像反向刺刀一樣向後突出，位於槍托應有的位置。這把刀刃使得發射器無法抵肩。如果你設法用軌道加速器揮向敵人，務必用這個擊中他們。"

#: .\ver_gunmods.json
msgid "stock"
msgstr "槍托"

#: .\ver_gunmods.json
msgid "cushioned handle"
msgid_plural "cushioned handles"
msgstr[0] "緩衝握把"

#: .\ver_gunmods.json
msgid ""
"A foam cushioned handle for the S-01 Rail Accelerator mk2 installed on the "
"picatinny rail where sights should go. It makes lugging the launcher by your"
" side just a bit more comfortable."
msgstr "一個泡沫緩衝握把，用於S-01軌道加速器mk2，安裝在皮卡汀尼導軌上，原本是瞄準鏡的位置。它讓隨身攜帶發射器稍微舒適一點。"

#: .\ver_gunmods.json
msgid "sights"
msgstr "瞄準具"

#: .\ver_gunmods.json
msgid "tuned magnetic accelerator"
msgid_plural "tuned magnetic accelerators"
msgstr[0] "調諧磁力加速器"

#: .\ver_gunmods.json
msgid ""
"Two long pieces of magnetized industrial-grade steel, each wrapped up in "
"copper wire meant to be used with the S-01 Rail Accelerator mk2, acting as a"
" further accelerator for projectiles.  Keep your hands away from it."
msgstr "兩塊長條磁化工業級鋼材，每塊都纏繞著銅線，用於S-01軌道加速器mk2，作為彈丸的進一步加速器。請勿用手觸碰。"

#: .\ver_gunmods.json
msgid "barrel"
msgstr "槍管"

#: .\ver_gunmods.json
msgid "plutonium battery"
msgid_plural "plutonium batterys"
msgstr[0] "鈈電池"

#: .\ver_gunmods.json
msgid ""
"A home-made cluster of ten plutonium sticks held together with bolted metal "
"rings that can be used to lessen the incredible power draw of the S-01 Rail "
"Accelerator mk2. Because of its makeshift nature, it is leaking radiation "
"until safely installed into the railgun's casing."
msgstr ""
"一個自制的由十根鈈棒組成的簇，用螺栓固定的金屬環固定在一起，可用於減輕S-01軌道加速器mk2的驚人功耗。由於其臨時性質，在安全安裝到軌道炮外殼之前，它會洩漏輻射。"

#: .\ver_gunmods.json
msgid "battery"
msgstr "電池"

#: .\ver_gunmods.json
msgid "incendiary battery"
msgid_plural "incendiary batterys"
msgstr[0] "燃燒電池"

#: .\ver_gunmods.json
msgid ""
"A container in the size of a can filled with incendiary powder and plutonium"
" slurry that can be inserted into the S-01 Rail Accelerator mk2. Doing so "
"will superheat the projectiles, causing the air they travel through to catch"
" on fire while greatly improving their penetrative power."
msgstr "一個罐子大小的容器，裝滿燃燒粉末和鈈漿，可插入S-01軌道加速器mk2。這樣做會使彈丸過熱，導致其穿過的空氣著火，同時大大提高其穿透力。"

#: .\ver_gunmods.json
msgid "shock battery"
msgid_plural "shock batterys"
msgstr[0] "電擊電池"

#: .\ver_gunmods.json
msgid ""
"A container in the size of a can filled with magnesium powder, concentrated "
"acid and plutonium slurry that can be inserted into the S-01 Rail "
"Accelerator mk2. Doing so will charge the projectiles with electricity that "
"will shock its targets."
msgstr "一個罐子大小的容器，裝滿鎂粉、濃縮酸和鈈漿，可插入S-01軌道加速器mk2。這樣做會使彈丸帶電，電擊其目標。"

#: .\ver_guns.json
msgid "S-01 Rail Accelerator mk2"
msgid_plural "S-01 Rail Accelerator mk2s"
msgstr[0] "S-01軌道加速器mk2"

#: .\ver_guns.json
msgid ""
"A crude, humongous hunk of tech scrap seated into the remains of what seems "
"like a minigun's frame and the widened receiver of a large caliber machine "
"gun, as well as numerous picatinny rails and odds and ends from other "
"weapons that are now impossible to identify, reinforced with superalloy and "
"ceramics covered in piezoelectric capacitors. The weapon launches rails at "
"such an overkill velocity that they shatter on impact. Carved near the blade"
" are the words 'With love, Shion' and a small carving of a canine-eared head"
" of a person with a smug grin, holding up a victory sign."
msgstr ""
"一塊粗糙、巨大的科技廢料，安裝在似乎是加特林機槍框架和大口徑機槍加寬機匣的殘骸中，以及眾多皮卡汀尼導軌和其他現已無法識別的武器零件，用高溫合金和覆蓋壓電電容器的陶瓷加固。該武器以過高的速度發射軌道，以至於它們在撞擊時碎裂。刀刃附近刻著“With"
" love, Shion”字樣，以及一個小雕刻，描繪了一個長著犬耳的人頭，帶著得意的笑容，比著勝利的手勢。"

#: .\ver_guns.json
msgid "semi auto"
msgstr "半自動"

#: .\ver_guns.json
msgid "auto"
msgstr "自動"

#: .\ver_guns.json
msgid "PTRS-41"
msgid_plural "PTRS-41s"
msgstr[0] "PTRS-41"

#: .\ver_guns.json
msgid ""
"The PTRS-41 is a semi-automatic anti-tank rifle produced and used by the "
"Soviets during World War II. It fires the powerful 14.5x114mm cartridge, but"
" getting ahold of those after the Cataclysm might prove to be a difficult "
"task."
msgstr ""
"PTRS-41是二戰期間蘇聯生產和使用的一種半自動反坦克步槍。它發射威力強大的14.5x114毫米彈藥，但在大災變後想要搞到這些子彈可能是一項艱鉅的任務。"

#: .\ver_items.json
msgid "kantele"
msgid_plural "kanteles"
msgstr[0] "康特勒琴"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'kantele', 'str_pl': 'kanteles'}
#: .\ver_items.json
